TechnologyDescriptionEn: Elongational Rheology Extruding Production Line (ERE Production Line)
column13: The revolutionary extruder, Elongational Rheology Extruder (ERE), has overturned polymer plasticizing and transporting process based on shearing rheology. Compared with conventional screw extruder, ERE has characteristics as follows: -  Weak Shearing Force -  Strong Elongational Force -  High Efficiency of Tansportation -  Less Molecular Weight Reduction -  Homogeneous Mixing and Dispersion -  Narrow Distribution of Residence Time -  Obvious Compatibilization Effect by Physical Means The ERE technology effectively solves the problem of molecular weight degradation of polymer materials during processing and difficult of processing extreme rheological behavior materials regarded as the worldwide problem. Whats more, it will greatly expands the application field of polymer materials, and promote the birth of a large number of new polymer materials & products with special functions. The application scope covers various industries from packing to automotive related to polymer materials.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: Microban Antimicrobial Technologies for Cleaner, Fresher & More Sustainable Plastic Products
column13: Microban antimicrobial protection works to eliminate bacteria, mould and mildew growth on plastic products and surfaces. Our innovative formulations have been proven to reduce the presence of Salmonella enterica, E. coli, MRSA and VRE by up to 99.9%. Microban technologies heavily contribute to sustainable product development by extending the lifespan of plastic articles. Through the inhibition of damaging microbes on a plastic surface, Microban helps to prevent premature product deterioration, visual discoloration and odours. Our customised additives are suitable for use in a range of polymers such as ABS, PP, PS, PE, LDPE, PVC and PC. Typical industry applications include food service, construction, consumer, and healthcare. Additive integration is safe, simple and seamless, and will not disrupt existing manufacturing processes. All Microban technologies have EPA registrations and are notified with the EU BPR. Specific formulations are also registered with the FDA and listed on EFSA.

TechNameEn: Filler & Color Masterbatch
TechnologyDescriptionEn: Filler Masterbatch is widely used in plastics industry for many economic benefits. Filler Masterbatch (or Calcium carbonate CaCO3 Filler Master batch) is compound of calcium carbonate powder and other additives, based on polymer carrier resin. This raw material normally is used for filling in plastics to replace a part of virgin polymer that is very expensive. It is the reason that Filler master batch brings cost savings solution to plastic manufacturers. Filler Masterbatch not only benefits to plastic manufacturers by keeping production costs down by replacing a part of the virgin polymer , but also improves production conditions, increases output. It increases calcium carbonate loading, make easier pelletization, cleaner manufacturing environment as well as many other physical and chemical properties of ended plastic products.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: Adhesive for plastics and rubber  WEICON VA 250 Black
column13: Adhesive for plastics and rubber  WEICON VA 250 Black  WEICON developed an adhesive for bonding plastics and rubber  the Contact Cyanoacrylate VA 250 Black.  The adhesive has a high viscosity and shows a residual elasticity after curing, therefore it is particularly suitable in ever changing climates. It is temperature resistant from -50C to +135C, ideal for bonding numerous rubber materials (e.g. solid rubber or cellular rubber), plastics as well as metal to plastic and shows an excellent peel and shock resistance.  Cyanoacrylates are cold-curing one-component adhesives that cure very quickly under the influence of humidity and pressure. They adhere very well even to smooth surfaces and bond almost all materials with and among each other within seconds. Due to their fast curing, cyanoacrylates are perfect adhesives for series production  be it in the automotive industry, consumer goods or in the manufacture of tools.

column13: To demonstrate the reproducible production of high-quality LSR components, ARBURG is showcasing an electric ALLROUNDER from the GOLDEN ELECTRIC series in an LSR version for the first time. The exhibit produces LSR lenses, each containing 33 optical fibres, in an automated and cost-effective manner and is equipped with two robotic systems: a linear MULTILIFT SELECT removes the lenses from the mould and places them on a cooling station. A six-axis robot delivers the injection moulded parts to a laser station where a DM code is applied. Every part is therefore 100 per cent traceable. LSR lenses are used, for example, in matrix headlights for cars to switch the LED main beam lights on and off depending on the situation. ARBURG's primary focus is on digitalisation and circular economy  the company is a leader in the industry in these fields thanks to its arburgXworld and arburgGREENworld programs. All machines exhibited at the stand are networked with the ARBURG host computer system ALS.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: Hyperion Smartcontrol
column13: The Hyperion SmartControl Touch is the latest innovation from Meech. The SmartControl Touch allows the user to remotely monitor and adjust the performance of connected Hyperion equipment, through a mobile phone, tablet or remote desktop. The SmartControl Touch also has the added benefit of an in-built touchscreen for ease of use. The ionising equipments performance is easily tracked by the SmartControl Touch, which uses Meechs Ion Current Monitoring Technology allowing the user to monitor the ionising performance and display data logging. As well as monitoring, the SmartControl Touch also makes it possible to adjust and control connected ionisers in order to optimise efficiency. A single SmartControl Touch has the capacity for up to six devices to be connected at a time (additional devices can be connected using an expansion kit). This means that in an application using multiple ionising bars, they can all be monitored and controlled through one SmartControl unit.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: ST BlowMoulding is the world-leading manufacturer of extrusion-blow moulding machines with parison suction technique. The sequential co-extrusion versions ASPI SeCo are used to generate a parison where two different plastic materials alternate according to a sequence defined in the mould recipe, and to obtain a blow moulded item with different mechanical characteristics along its axis. This is the ideal solution for 3D under the hood ducts, to cut the number of pieces being assembled and the consequent costs. The latest developments in ST BlowMoulding are aimed at production traceability, self-diagnostics and automatic process control. These are the objectives of devices such as the D-Print (a new generation parison marker, with both precision and speed 100 times above previous standards), the W-Print (to write data directly onto the parison and read it on the blow-moulded item) and the parison swell detector (an optical sensor to monitor the parison diameter).

column13: The FIMIC screen changer that allows both scraping and backflushing
column14: FIMICs design of the filter is an innovation,entirely different from the melt filter in the market.The design of FIMIC filter is basing on below ideas:Easy operation and maintenance,for different types of material and contamination,low operational cost,low melt loss,less worker needed,affordable spare part and flexible to work with different recycling extruders.FIMIC filter uses only one screen,punched or laser.Also,the filtration surface is very large comparing to other filters on the market.The most common issue for the melt filter on the market is too sensitive,the aggressive contamination could damage the parts on the filter and increases spare parts cost to the recyclers.FIMIC filter avoids this sensitivity on the mechanical parts,but to keep the high performance of filtration ability.With very fine filtration by our laser screen, low pressure and temperature during operation, the pellets produced from the machine which is installed with FIMIC filter has much better quality.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: XIFOS 33 , Market Leading 33 KV Anti-Static Ionising Power with Built-in Field Polarity Sensing and Adaptive Ionisation
column13: Offering market-leading performance, the intelligent XIFOS 33 static eliminator delivers 33 kV ionising power with built-in field polarity sensing and adaptive ionisation output to neutralise the actual charge. Ionisation distance and intelligence settings are easy to adjust locally, without the use of any tools. Status of the bar can be monitored easily by viewing the 5 green/red on-board LEDs. The XIFOS 33 is also compatible with IEC 61131-2 Type 1, 2 and 3 PLC inputs. Connectivity is via a standard 5-pin M12 connector, enabling customers to monitor its performance in any environment. Backwards compatible with Frasers NEOS 30 static eliminator, the XIFOS 33 is available in lengths of 600mm, 750mm, then in steps of 250mm to a maximum length of 6,000mm. Configured to neutralise charges at a range of 250mm to 1,500mm, the power of the XIFOS 33 makes it ideally suited to OEMs and end users with large winders, including slitters/rewinders, cast and blown film extruders, and laminators.

column14: Ultra Helix? 250 T2 Valve Gate Nozzles
column15: The new Ultra Helix? 250 T2 valve gate nozzle is designed for small part applications with difficult-to-access gate locations such as flip-top closures, cosmetic closures and other small, technical parts. It's the smallest nozzle in the Ultra Helix? family with only a 12mm diameter bore for gate access. This makes it possible to direct gate parts with gate vestige so clean it is often unmeasurable, lasting for millions of cycles, and offering mold makers more design flexibility. By direct-gating parts with the nozzle, molders can achieve resin savings, faster cycle times and better performance across a wider temperature range. Besides, the technology allows nozzle tip maintenance to be performed with no need to remove mold from injection molding machine. This new offer provides the same superior part quality, gate longevity and wide operating window that customers are used to, while providing more flexibility to mold even smaller, more technical parts with ultimate precision and quality.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: Umim Series Dynamic Injection Molding Machine
column13: Dynamic plasticizing and molding is the research achievement with international patent of the team of academician QuJinping who is the academician of Chinese Academy of Engineering and pacemaker of National Engineering Research Center of South China University of Technology for Polymer New Type Molding Equipment. Dynamic plasticizing and molding is the idea different from the traditional plasticizing injection process. Simply speaking, it is the technology to change the traditional stable plasticizing injection molding into the periodical dynamic plasticizing injection molding, which covers the basic technical principles such as dynamic solid compaction, dynamic smelting and plasticizing, and dynamic flux injection. The application of this plasticizing principle is capable of effectively increasing the fluidity, accelerating the injection process, providing uniform mold filling and greatly improving the mechanical property and quality of the product.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: Flexflow for Family Mold: Different Parts in A Single Shot and Aesthetic Performance At The Same Time. Efficiency and High Quality: No Longer Need to Choose Between The Two!
column13: Family molds for the cost and time efficient production of different parts in a single shot, have traditionally been associated with problems caused by traditional pin control methods, including poor balancing causing e. g. warpage issues.  FLEXflow - HRSflow's servo driven valve gate hot runner technology, provides a broad potential to improve the quality of the parts, to avoid cost for additional process tuning, to broaden the process window and to extend lifetime of the tool. Using FLEXflow servo driven valve gate technology to independently control stroke, timing and force of each individual pin, can overcome existing limitations in terms of close similarity in size, weight, wall section and volume, whilst ensuring all cavities are being filled simultaneously, preventing from overfeeding and flash formation.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: XB-3063 single shaft shredder
column13: XB-3063 single-shaft shredder consists of a motor, a reducer with rigid gears, a rotary shaft, imported rotary knife, fixed knife, frame, working platform, hydraulic ram and an independent electrical control cabinet. Fixed knives are installed on the frame behind the solid rotary shaft where the moving knives are bolted. Moving knives are specially designed into four-angel shape, when blunt customers could change the angel for recycling using. Moving knives are installed by screws, which is convenient for future maintenance. A hydraulic cylinder drove by hydraulic ram continually pushes the material chamber moving back and forward to get the material multi-angel shredding. Two travel switches are fitted near the side jampans to control the movement. A screen mesh is needed sometimes to ensure materials shredded even further. Single-shaft shredder is controlled by an independent electrical cabinet equipped with PLC system. The machine features start, stop, reverse functions. Also it is fitted with automatic overload return mechanism to prevent damage to working parts.

TechNameEn: PFOA Free PTFE Micropowders
TechnologyDescriptionEn: Tianshi makes PTFE micropowders & dispersions for use as additives in many industrial areas. Tianshi is the first PTFE micropowder manufacture in China that can meet the latest technical standards of the European Union. The lowest content of PFOA (in the list of 2B carcinogens) can reach 4ppb.  Tianshis PTFE micropowders can be added to polycarbonate and polyamide, as well as other plastics, to improve wear and to reduce the coefficient of friction. Also, they can combined with other flame retardants, and can also be blended with fluorocarbon or silicone oils to form very high performance lubricants and greases. PTFE based greases have extremely low friction, a wide operating temperature range, and a much longer usage life than conventional greases.

TechNameEn: Application of high performance light stabilizer in high-end nylon industry
TechnologyDescriptionEn: This series of products are suitable for nylon reinforcement and modification system. They contain special polar groups and have good compatibility with PA resin, and have excellent thermal stability and precipitation resistance. The product has both internal and external lubrication properties. Based on the special silicone structure, it can effectively improve the wettability and dispersion of glass fiber in PA melt, reduce the friction between glass fiber bundles, and improve the retention length of glass fiber. With less addition, the fluidity of the material can be improved obviously, the impact strength and modulus of the material can be improved, the surface floating fiber can be improved at the same time, and the good demoulding property and surface glossiness of the material products can be given. It can improve the dispersion of fillers and pigments in nylon and enhance the dyeability of nylon fiber. Improve the coloring power and stability of pigment.

column14: Single-Use / Season-Use Cutlery - biodegradable in soil, naturally heat-stable, simply natural
column15: Coffee spoons, cocktail stirrers moulded with nature2need Bioblend BT material grades are sturdy, high-temperature resistant, they come with a surprisingly high perceived quality; bright-white with a very glossy surface, coffee-brown with coffee-husk fill for a true natural look, or .... almost everything is possible. A much better product than the ones we all know made with traditional, oil-based plastics like PS or since recently with PLA/cPLA materials that are simply not degrading in nature. The cutlery is naturally heat stable until 100 deg Celsius (without annealing), biodegradable in controlled (e.g. industrial compost) and non-controlled (e.g. soil, landfill, roadside) conditions. The spoons and stirrers have a balanced elasticity to stiffness and are suitable for children as well; there is no risk of sharp edges when breaking. Low cost and high-quality levels will make it easier to convince everybody to finally change to more sustainable products! #protectournature

TechNameEn: PC Self-Bonding Liquid Silicone Elastomers
TechnologyDescriptionEn: More and more design requirements for soft and hard structures have promoted the progress of multi-component materials. Silicone and thermoplastic materials are widely used in two-color injection molding or insert injection molding, and this process requires different soft and hard materials. Very good bonding performance is needed to meet the request of design and processing. Momentive's new Silopren *LSR 27x9 and medical grade LSR 47x9 series Liquid Silicone Rubber are suitable for PC, PBT and Copolyester, and they could provide you with such a good solution. You do not need to use additional primers for bonding, or surface treatment of plastic substrates. You can get strong bonded products after direct injection of self-bonding series of liquid silicone rubber, which provides more space and freedom for software and hardware structure design.

TechnologyDescriptionEn: ULTRANOX LC Platform high-performance color stabilization and control solutions for polypropylene fibers
column13: The ULTRANOX LC platform is high-performance stabilization solutions for polypropylene fibers. The ULTRANOX LC platform has been designed for optimum color stability and control. This platform has good gas fading properties and excellent filterability. These products are fully formulated with metal stearates for fiber lubricity and are supplied in NDB blend form for improved HSE and handling. ULTRANOX LC platform can offer lower color development due to its patented stabilization system. The platform enables up to a reduction of 60% YI relative to current AO packages. ULTRANOX LC also improves upon color development of existing formulations using products with global food contact clearances and improves productivity due to lower off-spec production and reduced downtime. ULTRANOX LC products are used in polypropylene applications where color sensitivity is required such as polypropylene fibers, containers, and consumer goods.
